  "text": "Thirdly, androgens may influence melanoma risk through immune system suppression as a blockade of androgen signaling improved survival in melanoma patients [CITATION_1] . Additionally, as immunotherapy has been shown beneficial in the treatment for prostate cancer and melanoma, a common pathophysiologic mechanism of immune deficiency may be spurring the concurrent development of both cancers [CITATION_2] .",
